            <a href="https://www.dukechronicle.com/section/sports/columns">COLUMNS</a></span></div>

                <h1>Duke Football is on the verge</h1>
                
                                    <figure class="dom-art-container my-4">
                                                    <img src="https://snworksceo.imgix.net/dtc/60299a4c-0709-494d-8905-9a2c66b6203c.sized-1000x1000.jpg?w=1000" alt="Quarterback&#x20;Sean&#x20;Renfree&#x20;has&#x20;all&#x20;the&#x20;talent&#x20;he&#x20;needs&#x20;on&#x20;offense&#x20;to&#x20;continue&#x20;Duke&#x2019;s&#x20;recent&#x20;improvement." class="w-100">
                                                <div class="domphoto-caption mt-2 text-left text-md-right">
                            Quarterback Sean Renfree has all the talent he needs on offense to continue Duke’s recent improvement.

                                                             <aside class="photo-caption photo-credit d-block pl-1">
                                    <figcaption class="d-block">
                                                                                    Photo by <a href="https://www.dukechronicle.com/staff/lawzon-kurtz">Lawzon Kurtz</a> |
                                                                                                                                The Chronicle
                                                                            </figcaption>
                                </aside>
                            
                        </div>
                    </figure>
                
                                    <div class="row  mt-4 mb-0 mb-md-4">
                        <div class="col-12 col-md-6">
                            <aside class="author-name">
                                    
    
                                    
            By <a href="https://www.dukechronicle.com/staff/stephen-allan">Stephen Allan</a>
                                    
                                <div class="mt-1">
                                    <span class="can-localize">December 7, 2009 | 5:00am EST</span>
                                </div>
                            </aside>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-12 col-md-6 text-left text-md-right d-print-none">
                            <ul class="social-links list-unsyled list-inline mt-4 mt-md-0">
                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="http://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https://www.dukechronicle.com/article/2009/12/duke-football-verge" target="_blank" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="facebook" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fab fa-facebook"></i></a></li>
                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="http://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https://www.dukechronicle.com/article/2009/12/duke-football-verge&amp;text=Duke Football is on the verge" target="_blank" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="twitter" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fab fa-twitter"></i></a></li>
                                                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="mailto:?subject=Duke%20Football%20is%20on%20the%20verge%20|%20The%20Chronicle&amp;message=Check%20out%20this%20article%20from%20The%20Chronicle%3A%20https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dukechronicle.com%2Farticle%2F2009%2F12%2Fduke-football-verge" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="email" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fa fa-envelope"></i></a></li>
                                <li class="list-inline-item"><a href="#" onclick="window.print()" class="sends-events" data-ga-category="Share" data-ga-action="click" data-ga-label="facebook" data-ga-value="CURL"><i class="fas fa-print"></i></a></li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                
                <div class="article-content w-100 mb-4">
                                            <p>I admit that in this space, I have been pretty harsh on Duke Football.</p>
<p>I told you the Blue Devils had no shot against Kansas and that on the precipice of becoming bowl eligible, the odds of going to the postseason were heavily against Duke.</p>

                        <div class="inline-ad float-none float-md-left my-4 mr-0 mr-md-4 text-center d-print-none">
                            <!-- START gryphon/ads/rectangle-inline.tpl -->
            <div id="azk18664"></div>
    <!-- END gryphon/ads/rectangle-inline.tpl -->
                        </div>

                        <p>I always made it a point to tell it like it is, even if it meant basically saying that the Blue Devils were guaranteed to lose. So, for the last time this semester, I&rsquo;m going to keep it real and tell it like it is.</p>
<p>If David Cutcliffe can get faster defensive players, develop an offensive line whose average weight is over 300 pounds and mold Conner Vernon and Desmond Scott into the backyard athletes that Cutcliffe always craves, Duke won&rsquo;t just go bowling.</p>
<p>It could easily wind up in a BCS game by the time Vernon and Scott are seniors.</p>
<p>Preposterous? At the moment, yes, but that&rsquo;s not what I&rsquo;m getting at.</p>
<p>When you look at the successful programs of the decade&mdash;USC and Florida especially&mdash;you&rsquo;ll notice those three things that I just mentioned. If you&rsquo;re missing even one piece, you&rsquo;re not going to win your conference.*</p>
<p>*Unless you play in the Big Ten.</p>

                        <div class="inline-ad float-none float-md-left my-4 mr-0 mr-md-4 text-center d-print-none">
                            <!-- START gryphon/ads/rectangle-article-5.tpl -->
        <div id="azk5125"></div>
<!-- END gryphon/ads/rectangle-article-5.tpl -->
                        </div>

                                                                            <p>Charlie Weis will attest to that. He had as close to an NFL offense as you can get&mdash;but his lack of a defense is what ultimately cost him his job.</p>
<p>At this moment, Duke only has the potential offensive game-changers on its roster, and it&rsquo;s going to require some serious recruiting scores to get the defensive game-changers. But who would&rsquo;ve thought that just a couple of months into the job, Cutcliffe would convince Sean Renfree, the 10th-best quarterback prospect in the nation according to Scout.com, to come to a school that had won one game in the previous two years?</p>
<p>Now, Duke has actually won nine games in its previous two years, so going to high school seniors and pitching the program isn&rsquo;t nearly as difficult as it was before. There are definitely some potential studs in the pipeline: Matt Daniels and John Drew, a sophomore and a freshman, respectively, can easily develop into great players on the defensive side of the ball.</p>
<p>The Blue Devils are also trying to sway the interest of four-star defensive tackle John Watson and linebacker Danny Spond, the ninth-ranked middle linebacker in the country according to Scout. Get three or four of those top-tier recruits a class, and boom, you&rsquo;re suddenly a legitimate conference contender. North Carolina&rsquo;s defensive recruiting is what got it back to playing in bowls, and since Duke has a better coaching staff than the Tar Heels, the Blue Devils would be even better with a few big-time defensive recruits.</p>
                            

<div class="mc-signup my-4 p-4 text-center " id="mc-container" data-mc="58dfdea1a4">
    <h3>Get Overtime, all Duke athletics</h3>
    <p>Signup for our editorially curated, weekly newsletter. Cancel at any time.</p>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col col-md-8 offset-md-2">
            <form action="//dukechronicle.us4.list-manage.com/subscribe/post?u=c49dc69f492af7f2727860d0b&amp;id=58dfdea1a4" method="post">
